- Download

  Search | User TL |Retweets | Replies | Advanced Replies)

  Search
    Prefix (File prefix for results)
    Query (Twitter query, supports advanced queries)
    From (Start date of tweets YYYY-mm-dd HH:MM.SS)
    To (End date of tweets YYYY-mm-dd HH:MM.SS)
    Frequency (Interval min | hour | day | week | month | year)
  User TL
    Prefix (File prefix for results)
    Username (Selected user)
    From (Start date of tweets YYYY-mm-dd HH:MM.SS)
    To (End date of tweets YYYY-mm-dd HH:MM.SS)
    Frequency (Sampling frequency - min | hour | day | week | month | year)
  Retweets
    Prefix (Prefix of the file containing the original tweets)
    Min RTs (Minimum number of RTs required to download RTs)
   Comments
     Prefix (Prefix of the file containing the original tweets)
     Min Replies (Minimum number of comments required to download)
   Advanced Comments
     Prefix (Prefix of the file containing the original tweets)
     Min Replies (Minimum number of comments required to download)
     Last (Number of days since the tweet date)
     Frequency (Interval: min | hour | day | week | month | year)

- Tools:

   Merge files | Clean data

   Merge files
      input files
      output file

   Clean data
     Prefix (Prefix of the file with the original tweets)
     Positives: (List of included words)
     False positives: (List of excluded words)
     output file

- Graphs

   Prefix (Prefix of the file with comments or RTS)
   output Format graph:  gdf | GEXF
   Output file with the communities

Contents
    Prefix (Prefix of the file containing the tweets)

- Graphics 

  graphic type Tweets | Users

  Tweet Graphs

    prefix (Prefix for graph files)
    base_title (Base title of the graphs)
    time_zone (Time zone, default "Europe/Berlin")
    min_reach (The author will appear if the reach is greater than this amount)
    min_RTs (The author will appear if the number of RTs is greater than this amount)
    min_comments (Minimum number of comments to compare with RTs)
    show_topics (TRUE|FALSE TRUE if you want to show the topics)
    topics_file (Only if show_topics is TRUE)
    show_events (TRUE|FALSE TRUE if you want to annotate events)
    events_file (TRUE|FALSE FALSE if there are no annotations; if there are, the file name)
    show_users (TRUE|FALSE TRUE if you want to create facets per user. No more than 10 users)
    zoom FALSE (TRUE/|FALSE TRUE if zoom is desired)
    min_date_zoom: (Zoom start date yyyy-mm-dd HH:MM:SS Only if zoom is TRUE)
    max_date_zoom: (Zoom end date yyyy-mm-dd HH:MM:SS Only if zoom is TRUE)

  User Graphs

  prefix (Prefix for graph files)
  username (Name of the profile to analyze)
  base_title (Base title of the graphs)
  time_zone (Time zone, default "Europe/Berlin")
  show_topics (TRUE|FALSE) TRUE if topics are desired)
  topics_file (Only if show_topics is TRUE)
  show_events (TRUE|FALSE) TRUE if annotations are desired
  events_file (TRUE|FALSE) FALSE if no annotations exist; if there are annotations, the file name
  show_users (TRUE|FALSE TRUE if you want to create facets per user. No more than 10 users)

  En la parte derecha: Contexto y resultados
      En la parte superior Se indicará el proyecto activo y el numero de cuentas activas


